---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';
---

<ProjectLayout
  title="World Model Neural Network Architectures"
  period="Sep to Dec 2024"
  tags={['Reinforcement Learning', 'PyTorch', 'HPC', 'Weights & Biases', 'Python']}
  github="https://github.com/eralds/Investigating-World-Model-Neural-Network-Architectures"
  description="Investigating how different neural network architectures perform as transition function models within reinforcement learning world models."
>
  <div class="space-y-10 text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">
    <div>
      <h2 style="font-family: 'Inter Tight', Inter, sans-serif;" class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">Overview</h2>
      <p>
        World models are a core component in model-based reinforcement learning. They learn a compact internal representation
        of the environment so an agent can plan ahead without taking real actions. The quality of the learned transition
        function (predicting the next state given a current state and action) directly impacts agent performance.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4">
        This project systematically compared three neural network architectures as world model transition functions:
        <span class="font-semibold text-slate-800">MLP</span> (feedforward baseline),
        <span class="font-semibold text-slate-800">RNN</span> (recurrent, captures temporal dependencies), and
        <span class="font-semibold text-slate-800">Transformer</span> (attention-based, state-of-the-art sequence modelling).
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 style="font-family: 'Inter Tight', Inter, sans-serif;" class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">Methodology</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-3">
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent/60"></span>
          Designed and trained each architecture on the same RL environment transition data to enable fair comparison.
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent/60"></span>
          Ran large-scale multi-GPU experiments on Aalto University's <span class="font-semibold text-slate-800 whitespace-nowrap">Triton HPC cluster</span>.
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent/60"></span>
          Tracked all runs, metrics, and visualizations using <span class="font-semibold text-slate-800">Weights & Biases</span> for reproducibility and comparison.
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent/60"></span>
          Evaluated models on prediction accuracy, sample efficiency, and downstream agent performance.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 style="font-family: 'Inter Tight', Inter, sans-serif;" class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">Tech Stack</h2>
      <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
        {[
          { label: 'Framework', value: 'PyTorch' },
          { label: 'Experiment Tracking', value: 'Weights & Biases' },
          { label: 'Compute', value: 'Aalto Triton HPC (multi-GPU)' },
          { label: 'Language', value: 'Python' },
        ].map(({ label, value }) => (
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-100 bg-white p-4 shadow-sm">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-accent mb-1">{label}</p>
            <p class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-800">{value}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</ProjectLayout>
